main event: An unidentified object was observed in Ocean City, N.J. on July 23, 1961, moving erratically at varying altitudes.
interesting points: The object was detected both visually and on radar for about 10 minutes,The altitude of the object varied between 1500 and 3000 feet,The motion of the object was described as irregular and erratic with flashing lights,The radar operator noted that the object was not a typical target and its behavior was unlike known aircraft,The data was insufficient to draw any definitive conclusions about the object's nature.
